Remove or Delete a Key Qualifier

To reduce clutter and avoid reaching your org's limit for key qualifiers, remove and delete unnecessary key qualifiers from the system. To delete a key qualifier, you must first remove it from all the data lake object (DLO) fields that it’s associated with and then delete it. You can also just remove a key qualifier from a DLO field but not delete it from the system. Removing a key qualifier from a DLO field can potentially affect the accuracy of calculated insights, segments, activations, and API queries.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To remove and delete key qualifiers:	

One of these permission sets:

Data Cloud Admin
Data Cloud Marketing Admin
Identify the DLO fields associated with a key qualifier.
Before you remove or delete a key qualifier, you must remove it from its associated DLO fields. Identify all the DLO fields that share the key qualifier.
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Lake Objects tab.
Click the name of a DLO.
Click the dropdown next to any DLO field and select View Key Qualifiers.
In the Key Qualifier Details window, select the key qualifier that you want to delete (1) and note the DLO and DLO fields that are associated with it (2).
Remove the key qualifier from the DLO fields.
Before you can delete a key qualifier, you must remove it. You can also just remove it without deleting it.
On the Data Lake Objects tab, click the DLO that contains the field that you want to remove the key qualifier from.
Next to the DLO field that you want to remove the key qualifier from, click the dropdown, and select Remove Key Qualifier.
After you confirm the removal, the key qualifier is no longer associated with the DLO field.
If you’re only removing a key qualifier and not deleting it, you’re done.
Delete the key qualifier.
On the Data Lake Objects tab, click a DLO.
Click the dropdown next to any DLO field, and select Add Key Qualifier.
In the Add Key Qualifier window, select the key qualifier that you want to delete, click the dropdown next to it, and select Delete.
When prompted, confirm that you want to delete the key qualifier.
